CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 12, 1951, pg. 1, reads: "Personifies Typical Mother - Mrs. Eula Mae Robinson, 10 Davenport Street, who has lived in the Hill more than thirty-five years, was selected this week as a 'Typical Mother' by Mrs. Robert L. Vann.  Mrs. Robinson is the mother of six children and has to work to help the family's finances, but has always insisted that the children enter into all activities and cultural affairs in the city. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: "Mother of the Year" Eula Mae Robinson posed in home at 10 Davenport Street, Hill District
